Definition: disturbances in saltwater balance and symptoms of weakness and muscular cramps and twitching and convulsions and sometimes paralysis
Example: usually caused by a benign tumor of the cortex of the adrenal gland that leads to excess secretion of aldosterone
Synonyms: s_syndrome, syndrome, disturbances, in, saltwater, balance, and, symptoms, of, weakness, muscular, cramps, twitching, convulsions, sometimes, paralysis, usually, caused, by, a, benign, tumor, the, cortex, adrenal, gland, that, leads, to, excess, secretion, aldosterone
Category: noun.state
